I. You rob a man : he prosecutes you, and gets you punished : 

^ Here, as elsewhere, it may be observed, that the same words which are 
mentioned as names of motives, are also many of them names of passions, 
appetites, and affections : fictitious entities, which are framed only by con- 
sideiing pleasures or pains in some particular point of view. Some of them 
are also names of moral qualities. This branch of nomenclature is remark- 
ably entangled : to unravel it completely would take up a whole volume ; 
not a syllable of which would belong properly to the present design. 



