this they differ from private offences, but agree with semi-public 
ones. Here, as in semi-public offences, the extent of the mischief 
makes up for the uncertai/nty of it. 

11. In no case can satisfaction, given to any particular indi- 
vidual affected by them, be a sufScient ground for remitting 
punishment. In this they differ from private offences ; but agree 
with semi-public. 

