whoever is conmcted of stealing to be hanged. 

They might be styled ; the former, a simply imperative law ; the other, a 
punitory : but the pimitory, if it commands the punishment to be inflicted, 
and does not merely permit it, is as truly imperative as the other : only it is 
punitory besides, which the other is not. 

